</div>
<div id="node-48" class="node node-answer node-teaser clearfix" about="/answer/digital-analog-converter-d" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">

        <h2>
      <a href="/answer/digital-analog-converter-d">Digital to analog converter (D to A)</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="Digital to analog converter (D to A)" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><span property="sioc:num_replies" content="0" datatype="xsd:integer" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
      <div class="meta submitted">
            <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2014-03-26T16:58:14+00:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Updated: Tue, 2015-01-27 11:50</span>    </div>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>A digital to analog converter converts a digital signal to an audio signal. A simple example of this is the speaker out on your computers soundcard. A soundcard that has both A to D and D to A converters can be used to send audio to an outboard unit, eg. A reverb unit, and to send it back into the computer again (see <a href="/answer/insert">inserts</a>).</p>
</div></div></div>  </div>

      <div class="link-wrapper">
      <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first"><a href="/answer/digital-analog-converter-d" rel="tag" title="Digital to analog converter (D to A)">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about Digital to analog converter (D to A)</span></a></li>
<li class="comment_forbidden last"></li>
</ul>    </div>
  
  
</div>
<div id="node-47" class="node node-answer node-teaser clearfix" about="/answer/analog-digital-converter-d" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">

        <h2>
      <a href="/answer/analog-digital-converter-d">Analog to digital converter (A to D)</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="Analog to digital converter (A to D)" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><span property="sioc:num_replies" content="0" datatype="xsd:integer" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
      <div class="meta submitted">
            <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2014-03-26T16:57:06+00:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Updated: Tue, 2014-08-19 07:04</span>    </div>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>Soundcards have two main stages, <a href="/answer/preamp">preamp</a> and an analog to digital conversion stage. The preamp boosts the signal and the A to D stage converts that usable signal into the digital domain, which the computer can then process. Some soundcards come with only analog to digital converts, eg. Delta 1010, some RME interfaces, etc. These require external preamps.</p>
</div></div></div>  </div>

      <div class="link-wrapper">
      <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first"><a href="/answer/analog-digital-converter-d" rel="tag" title="Analog to digital converter (A to D)">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about Analog to digital converter (A to D)</span></a></li>
<li class="comment_forbidden last"></li>
</ul>    </div>
  
  
</div>
<div id="node-46" class="node node-answer node-teaser clearfix" about="/answer/preamp" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">

        <h2>
      <a href="/answer/preamp">Preamp</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="Preamp" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><span property="sioc:num_replies" content="0" datatype="xsd:integer" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
      <div class="meta submitted">
            <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2014-03-26T16:55:38+00:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Updated: Wed, 2014-08-13 15:32</span>    </div>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>A preamp boosts the input signal, from a mic or instrument, to a usable level. Most audio interfaces include a preamp.</p>
</div></div></div>  </div>

      <div class="link-wrapper">
      <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first"><a href="/answer/preamp" rel="tag" title="Preamp">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about Preamp</span></a></li>
