</ul>    </div>
  
  
</div>
<div id="node-45" class="node node-answer node-teaser clearfix" about="/answer/audio-interfacesoundcard" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">

        <h2>
      <a href="/answer/audio-interfacesoundcard">Audio interface/soundcard</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="Audio interface/soundcard" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><span property="sioc:num_replies" content="0" datatype="xsd:integer" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
      <div class="meta submitted">
            <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2014-03-26T16:54:26+00:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Updated: Thu, 2014-11-06 10:15</span>    </div>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>A device that gets audio in and out of your computer. All computers and laptops will have a basic built in sound card that will handle inputs (mic/line in) and outputs (to speakers/headphones). For professional audio you will need an additional soundcard/interface. These comes in various forms, USB, Firewire and PCI devices.</p>
<p><a href="/articles/understanding-recording-hardware">Understanding recording hardware</a></p></div></div></div>  </div>

      <div class="link-wrapper">
      <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first"><a href="/answer/audio-interfacesoundcard" rel="tag" title="Audio interface/soundcard">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about Audio interface/soundcard</span></a></li>
<li class="comment_forbidden last"></li>
</ul>    </div>
  
  
</div>
<div id="node-44" class="node node-answer node-teaser clearfix" about="/answer/ffado" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">

        <h2>
      <a href="/answer/ffado">FFADO</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="FFADO" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><span property="sioc:num_replies" content="0" datatype="xsd:integer" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
      <div class="meta submitted">
            <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2014-03-26T16:52:23+00:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Updated: Tue, 2014-08-19 07:12</span>    </div>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>FFADO stands for Free FireWire Audio Drivers. This is an open source device driver backend for <a href="/answer/jack">JACK</a>. If you want to use a firewire interface, check out the <a href="http://www.ffado.org/?q=devicesupport/list">FFADO</a> website to see which devices are supported.</p>
<p><img alt="" src="/sites/default/files/articles/FFADO.png" /></p>
</div></div></div>  </div>

