<div id="node-43" class="node node-answer node-teaser clearfix" about="/answer/pulse-audio" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">

        <h2>
      <a href="/answer/pulse-audio">Pulse Audio</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="Pulse Audio" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><span property="sioc:num_replies" content="0" datatype="xsd:integer" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
      <div class="meta submitted">
            <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2014-03-26T16:49:40+00:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Updated: Tue, 2014-08-19 07:20</span>    </div>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>Pulse audio is a sound server that uses <a href="/answer/alsa">ALSA</a> as it's backend. It is more geared towards general desktop audio. While it is useful for these purposes, pulse audio isn't used for any audio production software.</p>
</div></div></div>  </div>

      <div class="link-wrapper">
      <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first"><a href="/answer/pulse-audio" rel="tag" title="Pulse Audio">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about Pulse Audio</span></a></li>
<li class="comment_forbidden last"></li>
